text: Moorslede is a municipality in the Belgian province of West Flanders. Moorslede comprises the towns of Dadizele and Moorslede itself. In 2007, 10697 people lived there. It is at 50° 53 North, 03° 03 East. == Personality == Constant Lievens (1856-1893), the apostle of the Chota Nagpur, was born in Moorslede. == History == The 1950 World Cycling Championshipwas held in Moorslede and was won by Briek Schotte. == References == == Other websites == * www.moorslede.be Category:Municipalities of West Flanders
